cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.SI

The paper discusses an algorithm for solving optimization problems with mixed-norm regularization, which is commonly used in machine learning and statistics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the theoretical analysis of the proposed algorithm, which involves numerical analysis and optimization, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) another likely category. The proposed algorithm is applicable to regression and classification problems, which are commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a screening method to reduce the computational cost, which is related to optimization and machine learning, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) another possible category.
